cd ~/Desktop/GitDemo
git status
git branch GitWork
git checkout GitWork
touch hello.xml
notepad hello.xml
git add hello.xml
git commit -m "Added hello.xml in GitWork"
git checkout master
notepad hello.xml
git add hello.xml
git commit -m "Added hello.xml in master"
git log --oneline --graph --decorate --all
git diff master GitWork
git merge GitWork
notepad hello.xml
git add hello.xml
git commit -m "Resolved merge conflict"
git status
notepad .gitignore
git add .gitignore
git commit -m "Updated gitignore"
git branch
git branch -d GitWork
git log --oneline --graph --decorate
git status


When notepad hello.xml opens the first time, type:

<message>Hello from GitWork Branch</message>


When notepad hello.xml opens the second time, replace it with:

<message>Hello from Master Branch</message>


After the merge conflict, replace the conflict markers with:

<message>Hello from Master Branch and GitWork Branch</message>
